This paper deals with machine learning models and privacy concerns, which are common topics in the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the need for privacy-preserving techniques, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of multiple datasets from different clients suggests the possibility of dealing with large amounts of data, which is a topic in the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also mentions the use of Software as a Service (SaaS), which is related to the sub-category of cs.DB (Databases). Finally, the paper mentions the cold-start problem, which is a topic in the sub-category of cs.CY (Computational Complexity).
